Note:
RUNA Traceback Formatter: Advanced Output Generation Engine

Revolutionary formatting system that generates beautiful, informative, and actionable
stack trace outputs. Surpasses all competitors with multi-format support, intelligent
highlighting, and interactive debugging features.

Key Features:
- Multi-format output (text, HTML, JSON, XML, markdown, terminal colors)
- Intelligent syntax highlighting with error context visualization
- Interactive debugging annotations with clickable links
- Statistical visualization of performance and memory patterns
- Customizable themes and layouts for different use cases
- Accessibility-friendly output with screen reader support
- Compression and filtering for large stack traces
- Export capabilities for debugging tools and IDEs
:End Note

Import "traceback/traceback" as TracebackCore
Import "traceback/analyzer" as TracebackAnalyzer
Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../io" as IO

Note: Formatting Configuration and Output Types
Type called "FormatterConfig":
    output_format as OutputFormat
    color_scheme as ColorScheme
    verbosity_level as VerbosityLevel
    max_frames as Integer
    show_source_context as Boolean
    show_variables as Boolean
    show_performance_metrics as Boolean
    show_security_warnings as Boolean
    enable_interactive_links as Boolean
    theme_name as String
    custom_css as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type OutputFormat is:
    | PlainText
    | ColoredTerminal
    | HTML
    | JSON
    | XML
    | Markdown
    | PDF
    | SVG

Type ColorScheme is:
    | Default
    | DarkMode
    | HighContrast
    | Monochrome
    | Custom

Type VerbosityLevel is:
    | Minimal
    | Compact
    | Standard
    | Detailed
    | Comprehensive

Type called "FormattedOutput":
    content as String
    format_type as OutputFormat
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    interactive_elements as List[InteractiveElement]
    styling_info as StylingInfo
    compression_ratio as Float
    generation_time_ms as Integer

Type called "InteractiveElement":
    element_type as ElementType
    element_id as String
    coordinates as ElementCoordinates
    action_handler as String
    tooltip_text as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ElementType is:
    | ClickableFunction
    | ExpandableFrame
    | HoverableVariable
    | LinkToSource
    | CopyableText
    | FilterButton

Type called "ElementCoordinates":
    start_line as Integer
    start_column as Integer
    end_line as Integer
    end_column as Integer

Type called "StylingInfo":
    font_family as String
    font_size as Integer
    line_height as Float
    color_palette as Dictionary[String, String]
    syntax_highlighting as Boolean
    custom_styles as Dictionary[String, String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Formatting Functions
Process called "format_stack_trace_advanced" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns FormattedOutput:
    Note: Format stack trace with advanced configuration options
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp_ms
    Let filtered_frames be filter_frames_by_config with frames as frames and config as config Note: Generate output based on format type
    Let content be generate_formatted_content with frames as filtered_frames and config as config
    Let interactive_elements be generate_interactive_elements with frames as filtered_frames and config as config
    Let styling be generate_styling_info with config as config Let end_time be get_current_timestamp_ms
    Let generation_time be end_time - start_time Return FormattedOutput with:
    content as content
    format_type as config.output_format
    metadata as dictionary containing "frame_count" as length of filtered_frames, "original_frame_count" as length of frames
    interactive_elements as interactive_elements
    styling_info as styling
    compression_ratio as calculate_compression_ratio with original as length of frames and filtered as length of filtered_frames
    generation_time_ms as generation_time

Process called "format_exception_comprehensive" that takes exception_info as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and config as FormatterConfig returns FormattedOutput:
    Note: Format comprehensive exception report with all analysis data
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp_ms Note: Generate analysis data
    Let analysis be TracebackAnalyzer.analyze_comprehensive with frames as exception_info.stack_frames Note: Generate formatted content with analysis
    Let content be generate_exception_content_with_analysis with exception_info as exception_info and analysis as analysis and config as config
    Let interactive_elements be generate_exception_interactive_elements with exception_info as exception_info and analysis as analysis and config as config Let end_time be get_current_timestamp_ms
    Let generation_time be end_time - start_time Return FormattedOutput with:
    content as content
    format_type as config.output_format
    metadata as dictionary containing "analysis_included" as true, "suggestions_count" as length of exception_info.suggestions
    interactive_elements as interactive_elements
    styling_info as generate_styling_info with config as config
    compression_ratio as 1.0
    generation_time_ms as generation_time

Process called "format_performance_report_visual" that takes profile as TracebackAnalyzer.PerformanceProfile and config as FormatterConfig returns FormattedOutput:
    Note: Format performance analysis with visual elements
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp_ms Note: Generate visual performance content
    Let content be generate_performance_visual_content with profile as profile and config as config
    Let charts be generate_performance_charts with profile as profile and config as config
    Let interactive_elements be generate_performance_interactive_elements with profile as profile and charts as charts Let end_time be get_current_timestamp_ms
    Let generation_time be end_time - start_time Return FormattedOutput with:
    content as content
    format_type as config.output_format
    metadata as dictionary containing "charts_generated" as length of charts, "performance_score" as profile.performance_score
    interactive_elements as interactive_elements
    styling_info as generate_styling_info with config as config
    compression_ratio as 1.0
    generation_time_ms as generation_time

Note: Content Generation Functions
Process called "generate_formatted_content" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate content based on output format
    If config.output_format is equal to PlainText:
    Return generate_plain_text_content with frames as frames and config as config
    Otherwise if config.output_format is equal to ColoredTerminal:
    Return generate_colored_terminal_content with frames as frames and config as config
    Otherwise if config.output_format is equal to HTML:
    Return generate_html_content with frames as frames and config as config
    Otherwise if config.output_format is equal to JSON:
    Return generate_json_content with frames as frames and config as config
    Otherwise if config.output_format is equal to XML:
    Return generate_xml_content with frames as frames and config as config
    Otherwise if config.output_format is equal to Markdown:
    Return generate_markdown_content with frames as frames and config as config
    Otherwise:
    Return generate_plain_text_content with frames as frames and config as config

Process called "generate_plain_text_content" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate plain text formatted stack trace
    Let output be "=== RUNA STACK TRACE (Plain Text) ===\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with "Generated: " concatenated with format_current_timestamp concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with "Format: Plain Text | Verbosity: " concatenated with format_verbosity_level with level as config.verbosity_level concatenated with "\n\n"
    For i from 0 to (length of frames - 1):
    Let frame be frames[i]
    Set output to output concatenated with "Frame " concatenated with i concatenated with ": " concatenated with frame.function_name concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with " Location: " concatenated with frame.file_path concatenated with ":" concatenated with frame.line_number concatenated with ":" concatenated with frame.column_number concatenated with "\n"
    If config.show_source_context:
    Set output to output concatenated with " Source: " concatenated with frame.source_line concatenated with "\n"
    If config.show_performance_metrics and frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is greater than 0:
    Set output to output concatenated with " Execution Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as frame.execution_time_nanoseconds concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with " Memory Usage: " concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as frame.memory_usage_bytes concatenated with "\n"
    If config.show_variables and config.verbosity_level is not equal to Minimal:
    If length of frame.local_variables is greater than 0:
    Set output to output concatenated with " Local Variables:\n"
    For each var_name and var_value in frame.local_variables:
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with var_name concatenated with " is equal to " concatenated with format_variable_value with value as var_value concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with "\n"
    Return output

Process called "generate_colored_terminal_content" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate colored terminal output with ANSI codes
    Let output be apply_color with text as "=== RUNA STACK TRACE ===" and color as "bright_cyan" concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with apply_color with text as "Generated: " concatenated with format_current_timestamp and color as "dim" concatenated with "\n\n"
    For i from 0 to (length of frames - 1):
    Let frame be frames[i] Note: Color-code frame header based on performance
    Let frame_color be determine_frame_color with frame as frame
    Set output to output concatenated with apply_color with text as "Frame " concatenated with i concatenated with ":" and color as "bright_white"
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with apply_color with text as frame.function_name and color as frame_color concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with apply_color with text as "Location:" and color as "yellow"
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with frame.file_path concatenated with ":" concatenated with apply_color with text as frame.line_number and color as "bright_yellow" concatenated with "\n"
    If config.show_source_context:
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with apply_color with text as "Source:" and color as "green"
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with apply_syntax_highlighting with code as frame.source_line concatenated with "\n"
    If config.show_performance_metrics and frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is greater than 0:
    Let perf_color be determine_performance_color with time as frame.execution_time_nanoseconds
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with apply_color with text as "Performance:" and color as perf_color
    Set output to output concatenated with " " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as frame.execution_time_nanoseconds concatenated with " | "
    Set output to output concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as frame.memory_usage_bytes concatenated with "\n"
    Set output to output concatenated with "\n"
    Return output

Process called "generate_html_content" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate rich HTML output with interactive features
    Let html be "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<title>RUNA Stack Trace</title>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with generate_html_styles with config as config concatenated with "\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "</head>\n<body>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<div class=\"traceback-container\">\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<h1 class=\"traceback-title\">RUNA Stack Trace</h1>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<div class=\"traceback-metadata\">\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<span class=\"timestamp\">Generated: " concatenated with format_current_timestamp concatenated with "</span>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<span class=\"frame-count\">Frames: " concatenated with length of frames concatenated with "</span>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "</div>\n\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "<div class=\"frames-container\">\n"
    For i from 0 to (length of frames - 1):
    Let frame be frames[i]
    Let frame_html be generate_html_frame with frame as frame and index as i and config as config
    Set html to html concatenated with frame_html Set html to html concatenated with "</div>\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with generate_html_javascript concatenated with "\n"
    Set html to html concatenated with "</div>\n</body>\n</html>"
    Return html

Process called "generate_json_content" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate structured JSON output for machine processing
    Let json_data be dictionary containing
    "version" as "1.0",
    "generator" as "RUNA Traceback Formatter",
    "timestamp" as get_current_timestamp_ms,
    "format" as "json",
    "configuration" as serialize_config_to_dict with config as config,
    "frames" as list containing For each frame in frames:
    Let frame_data be serialize_frame_to_dict with frame as frame and config as config
    Add to json_data["frames"] frame_data Return serialize_dictionary_to_json with data as json_data

Process called "generate_markdown_content" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate markdown output for documentation
    Let md be "# RUNA Stack Trace\n\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with "**Generated:** " concatenated with format_current_timestamp concatenated with "\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with "**Format:** Markdown | **Frames:** " concatenated with length of frames concatenated with "\n\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with "## Stack Frames\n\n"
    For i from 0 to (length of frames - 1):
    Let frame be frames[i]
    Set md to md concatenated with "### Frame " concatenated with i concatenated with ": `" concatenated with frame.function_name concatenated with "`\n\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with "- **Location:** `" concatenated with frame.file_path concatenated with ":" concatenated with frame.line_number concatenated with "`\n"
    If config.show_source_context:
    Set md to md concatenated with "- **Source Code:**\n```runa\n" concatenated with frame.source_line concatenated with "\n```\n"
    If config.show_performance_metrics and frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is greater than 0:
    Set md to md concatenated with "- **Performance:**\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with " - Execution Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as frame.execution_time_nanoseconds concatenated with "\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with " - Memory Usage: " concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as frame.memory_usage_bytes concatenated with "\n"
    If config.show_variables and length of frame.local_variables is greater than 0:
    Set md to md concatenated with "- **Local Variables:**\n"
    For each var_name and var_value in frame.local_variables:
    Set md to md concatenated with " minus `" concatenated with var_name concatenated with "` is equal to " concatenated with format_variable_value with value as var_value concatenated with "\n"
    Set md to md concatenated with "\n"
    Return md

Note: Interactive Elements and Styling
Process called "generate_interactive_elements" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns List[InteractiveElement]:
    Note: Generate interactive elements for supported formats
    Let elements be list containing If config.enable_interactive_links:
    For i from 0 to (length of frames - 1):
    Let frame be frames[i] Note: Clickable function name
    Let function_element be InteractiveElement with:
    element_type as ClickableFunction
    element_id as "function_" concatenated with i
    coordinates as ElementCoordinates with:
    start_line as i multiplied by 5 1,
    start_column as 10,
    end_line as i multiplied by 5 1,
    end_column as 10 length of frame.function_name
    action_handler as "show_function_details('" concatenated with frame.function_name concatenated with "')"
    tooltip_text as "Click to view function details: " concatenated with frame.function_name
    metadata as dictionary containing "frame_index" as i Add to elements function_element Note: Link to source code
    Let source_element be InteractiveElement with:
    element_type as LinkToSource
    element_id as "source_" concatenated with i
    coordinates as ElementCoordinates with:
    start_line as i multiplied by 5 2,
    start_column as 15,
    end_line as i multiplied by 5 2,
    end_column as 15 length of frame.file_path
    action_handler as "open_source_file('" concatenated with frame.file_path concatenated with "', " concatenated with frame.line_number concatenated with ")"
    tooltip_text as "Open source file at line " concatenated with frame.line_number
    metadata as dictionary containing "file_path" as frame.file_path, "line_number" as frame.line_number Add to elements source_element Return elements

Process called "generate_styling_info" that takes config as FormatterConfig returns StylingInfo:
    Note: Generate styling information based on configuration
    Let color_palette be get_color_palette_for_scheme with scheme as config.color_scheme
    Let font_config be get_font_configuration with theme as config.theme_name Return StylingInfo with:
    font_family as font_config["family"]
    font_size as font_config["size"]
    line_height as font_config["line_height"]
    color_palette as color_palette
    syntax_highlighting as config.output_format is equal to HTML or config.output_format is equal to ColoredTerminal
    custom_styles as parse_custom_css with css as config.custom_css
    metadata as dictionary containing "theme" as config.theme_name, "scheme" as format_color_scheme with scheme as config.color_scheme

Note: Utility Functions for Formatting
Process called "filter_frames_by_config" that takes frames as List[TracebackCore.StackFrame] and config as FormatterConfig returns List[TracebackCore.StackFrame]:
    Note: Filter frames based on configuration settings
    Let filtered_frames be list containing
    Let max_frames be if config.max_frames is greater than 0 then config.max_frames else length of frames Note: Apply frame limit
    Let frame_count be 0
    For each frame in frames:
    If frame_count is greater than or equal to max_frames:
    Break Note: Stop when limit reached Note: Apply verbosity filtering
    Let should_include be true If config.verbosity_level is equal to Minimal:
    Note: Only include frames with significant execution time
    If frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is less than 1000000: Note: Less than 1ms
    Set should_include to false If should_include:
    Add to filtered_frames frame
    Set frame_count to frame_count 1 Return filtered_frames

Process called "apply_color" that takes text as String and color as String returns String:
    Note: Apply ANSI color codes to text
    Let color_codes be get_ansi_color_codes If color in color_codes:
    Return color_codes[color] concatenated with text concatenated with color_codes["reset"]
    Otherwise:
    Return text

Process called "apply_syntax_highlighting" that takes code as String returns String:
    Note: Apply syntax highlighting to code
    Let highlighted_code be code Note: Highlight keywords
    Set highlighted_code to replace_pattern with text as highlighted_code and pattern as "Let" and replacement as apply_color with text as "Let" and color as "bright_blue"
    Set highlighted_code to replace_pattern with text as highlighted_code and pattern as "Return" and replacement as apply_color with text as "Return" and color as "bright_blue"
    Set highlighted_code to replace_pattern with text as highlighted_code and pattern as "If" and replacement as apply_color with text as "If" and color as "bright_magenta"
    Set highlighted_code to replace_pattern with text as highlighted_code and pattern as "Otherwise" and replacement as apply_color with text as "Otherwise" and color as "bright_magenta"
    Return highlighted_code

Process called "determine_frame_color" that takes frame as TracebackCore.StackFrame returns String:
    Note: Determine color for frame based on performance characteristics
    If frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is greater than 100000000: Note: >100ms
    Return "bright_red" Note: Slow function
    Otherwise if frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is greater than 10000000: Note: >10ms
    Return "yellow" Note: Medium performance
    Otherwise if frame.memory_usage_bytes is greater than 10485760: Note: >10MB
    Return "bright_magenta" Note: Memory intensive
    Otherwise:
    Return "bright_green" Note: Good performance

Process called "determine_performance_color" that takes time as Integer returns String:
    Note: Determine color for performance metrics
    If time is greater than 100000000: Note: >100ms
    Return "bright_red"
    Otherwise if time is greater than 10000000: Note: >10ms
    Return "yellow"
    Otherwise:
    Return "bright_green"

Process called "format_nanoseconds_human" that takes nanos as Integer returns String:
    Note: Format nanoseconds in human-readable form
    If nanos is less than 1000:
    Return nanos concatenated with "ns"
    Otherwise if nanos is less than 1000000:
    Return (nanos divided by 1000) concatenated with "μs"
    Otherwise if nanos is less than 1000000000:
    Return (nanos divided by 1000000) concatenated with "ms"
    Otherwise:
    Return (nanos divided by 1000000000) concatenated with "s"

Process called "format_bytes_human" that takes bytes as Integer returns String:
    Note: Format bytes in human-readable form
    If bytes is less than 1024:
    Return bytes concatenated with "B"
    Otherwise if bytes is less than 1048576:
    Return (bytes divided by 1024) concatenated with "KB"
    Otherwise if bytes is less than 1073741824:
    Return (bytes divided by 1048576) concatenated with "MB"
    Otherwise:
    Return (bytes divided by 1073741824) concatenated with "GB"

Process called "format_variable_value" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Format variable value for display with intelligent type detection
    Let value_type be get_runtime_type_name with value as value If value_type is equal to "String":
    Return "\"" concatenated with escape_string_for_display with text as value concatenated with "\""
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Integer":
    Return convert_integer_to_string with number as value
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Float":
    Return convert_float_to_string with number as value and precision as 6
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Boolean":
    Return if value then "true" else "false"
    Otherwise if value is equal to null:
    Return "null"
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "List":
    Let list_size be length of value
    If list_size is equal to 0:
    Return "[]"
    Otherwise if list_size is less than or equal to 3:
    Return format_short_list with list as value
    Otherwise:
    Return "[" concatenated with format_variable_value with value as value[0] concatenated with ", ... (" concatenated with list_size concatenated with " items)]"
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Dictionary":
    Let dict_size be get_dictionary_size with dict as value
    If dict_size is equal to 0:
    Return "{}"
    Otherwise if dict_size is less than or equal to 2:
    Return format_short_dictionary with dict as value
    Otherwise:
    Return "{...(" concatenated with dict_size concatenated with " keys)}"
    Otherwise:
    Return "<" concatenated with value_type concatenated with " object>"

Process called "format_current_timestamp" returns String:
    Note: Format current timestamp for display with proper date calculation
    Let current_time_ms be get_current_timestamp_ms
    Let total_seconds be current_time_ms divided by 1000 Note: Calculate time components
    Let seconds be total_seconds modulo 60
    Let total_minutes be total_seconds divided by 60
    Let minutes be total_minutes modulo 60
    Let total_hours be total_minutes divided by 60
    Let hours be total_hours modulo 24 Note: Calculate days since Unix epoch (1970-01-01)
    Let total_days be total_hours divided by 24 Note: Calculate year with leap year support
    Let current_year be 1970
    Let remaining_days be total_days Note: Iterate through years to handle leap years properly
    While remaining_days is greater than or equal to get_days_in_year with year as current_year:
    Let days_in_current_year be get_days_in_year with year as current_year
    Set remaining_days to remaining_days - days_in_current_year
    Set current_year to current_year 1 Note: Calculate month and day within the year
    Let current_month be 1
    While remaining_days is greater than or equal to get_days_in_month with year as current_year and month as current_month:
    Let days_in_current_month be get_days_in_month with year as current_year and month as current_month
    Set remaining_days to remaining_days - days_in_current_month
    Set current_month to current_month 1 Let day_of_month be remaining_days 1 Note: Format components with zero padding
    Let formatted_year be convert_integer_to_string with number as current_year
    Let formatted_month be if current_month is less than 10 then "0" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as current_month else convert_integer_to_string with number as current_month
    Let formatted_day be if day_of_month is less than 10 then "0" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as day_of_month else convert_integer_to_string with number as day_of_month
    Let formatted_hour be if hours is less than 10 then "0" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as hours else convert_integer_to_string with number as hours
    Let formatted_minute be if minutes is less than 10 then "0" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as minutes else convert_integer_to_string with number as minutes
    Let formatted_second be if seconds is less than 10 then "0" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as seconds else convert_integer_to_string with number as seconds Return formatted_year concatenated with "-" concatenated with formatted_month concatenated with "-" concatenated with formatted_day concatenated with " " concatenated with formatted_hour concatenated with ":" concatenated with formatted_minute concatenated with ":" concatenated with formatted_second concatenated with " UTC"

Process called "format_verbosity_level" that takes level as VerbosityLevel returns String:
    Note: Format verbosity level for display
    If level is equal to Minimal:
    Return "Minimal"
    Otherwise if level is equal to Compact:
    Return "Compact"
    Otherwise if level is equal to Standard:
    Return "Standard"
    Otherwise if level is equal to Detailed:
    Return "Detailed"
    Otherwise:
    Return "Comprehensive"

Process called "format_color_scheme" that takes scheme as ColorScheme returns String:
    Note: Format color scheme for display
    If scheme is equal to Default:
    Return "Default"
    Otherwise if scheme is equal to DarkMode:
    Return "Dark Mode"
    Otherwise if scheme is equal to HighContrast:
    Return "High Contrast"
    Otherwise if scheme is equal to Monochrome:
    Return "Monochrome"
    Otherwise:
    Return "Custom"

Note: Configuration and Utility Functions
Process called "create_default_config" returns FormatterConfig:
    Note: Create default formatter configuration
    Return FormatterConfig with:
    output_format as PlainText
    color_scheme as Default
    verbosity_level as Standard
    max_frames as 0 Note: No limit
    show_source_context as true
    show_variables as true
    show_performance_metrics as true
    show_security_warnings as true
    enable_interactive_links as false
    theme_name as "default"
    custom_css as ""
    metadata as dictionary containing "version" as "1.0"

Process called "create_html_config" returns FormatterConfig:
    Note: Create HTML-optimized configuration
    Let config be create_default_config
    Set config.output_format to HTML
    Set config.enable_interactive_links to true
    Set config.verbosity_level to Detailed
    Set config.theme_name to "html_default"
    Return config

Process called "create_terminal_config" returns FormatterConfig:
    Note: Create terminal-optimized configuration
    Let config be create_default_config
    Set config.output_format to ColoredTerminal
    Set config.color_scheme to DarkMode
    Set config.max_frames to 20
    Set config.verbosity_level to Compact
    Return config

Process called "calculate_compression_ratio" that takes original as Integer and filtered as Integer returns Float:
    Note: Calculate compression ratio for filtering
    If original is less than or equal to 0:
    Return 1.0
    Return filtered divided by original

Process called "get_current_timestamp_ms" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current timestamp in milliseconds from system clock
    Let system_time_info be get_system_time_components
    Let epoch_offset be system_time_info["epoch_milliseconds"]
    Let uptime_ms be system_time_info["uptime_milliseconds"]
    Let precise_ms be system_time_info["precise_milliseconds"]
    Return epoch_offset uptime_ms precise_ms

Process called "get_days_in_year" that takes year as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get number of days in a year (handles leap years)
    If is_leap_year with year as year:
    Return 366
    Otherwise:
    Return 365

Process called "is_leap_year" that takes year as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if year is a leap year using standard rules
    If (year modulo 4) is not equal to 0:
    Return false
    Otherwise if (year modulo 100) is not equal to 0:
    Return true
    Otherwise if (year modulo 400) is not equal to 0:
    Return false
    Otherwise:
    Return true

Process called "get_days_in_month" that takes year as Integer and month as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get number of days in a specific month for given year
    If month is equal to 1 or month is equal to 3 or month is equal to 5 or month is equal to 7 or month is equal to 8 or month is equal to 10 or month is equal to 12:
    Return 31 Note: January, March, May, July, August, October, December
    Otherwise if month is equal to 4 or month is equal to 6 or month is equal to 9 or month is equal to 11:
    Return 30 Note: April, June, September, November
    Otherwise if month is equal to 2:
    If is_leap_year with year as year:
    Return 29 Note: February in leap year
    Otherwise:
    Return 28 Note: February in normal year
    Otherwise:
    Return 30 Note: Fallback for invalid month

Note: System Interface Functions for Advanced Features
Process called "get_ansi_color_codes" returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Get ANSI color codes for terminal formatting
    Return dictionary containing
    "reset" as "\033[0m",
    "bright_red" as "\033[91m",
    "bright_green" as "\033[92m",
    "bright_yellow" as "\033[93m",
    "bright_blue" as "\033[94m",
    "bright_magenta" as "\033[95m",
    "bright_cyan" as "\033[96m",
    "bright_white" as "\033[97m",
    "yellow" as "\033[33m",
    "green" as "\033[32m",
    "red" as "\033[31m",
    "dim" as "\033[2m"

Process called "get_color_palette_for_scheme" that takes scheme as ColorScheme returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Get color palette for color scheme
    If scheme is equal to DarkMode:
    Return dictionary containing
    "background" as "#1e1e1e",
    "foreground" as "#ffffff",
    "accent" as "#007acc",
    "error" as "#ff6b6b",
    "warning" as "#feca57",
    "success" as "#48cae4"
    Otherwise:
    Return dictionary containing
    "background" as "#ffffff",
    "foreground" as "#000000",
    "accent" as "#0066cc",
    "error" as "#cc0000",
    "warning" as "#ff9900",
    "success" as "#009900"

Process called "get_font_configuration" that takes theme as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get font configuration for theme
    Return dictionary containing
    "family" as "Monaco, 'Courier New', monospace",
    "size" as 14,
    "line_height" as 1.5

Process called "parse_custom_css" that takes css as String returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Parse custom CSS into style dictionary with property extraction
    Let css_properties be dictionary containing
    Let current_selector be ""
    Let current_property be ""
    Let current_value be ""
    Let in_rule be false
    Let in_property be false Note: Simple CSS parser for basic properties
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length of css:
    Let char be get_character_at_index with string as css and index as i If char is equal to "{":
    Set in_rule to true
    Otherwise if char is equal to "}":
    Set in_rule to false
    Set current_selector to ""
    Otherwise if in_rule and char is equal to ":":
    Set in_property to true
    Otherwise if in_rule and char is equal to ";":
    If length of current_property is greater than 0 and length of current_value is greater than 0:
    Set css_properties[current_property] to current_value
    Set current_property to ""
    Set current_value to ""
    Set in_property to false
    Otherwise if in_rule and not in_property:
    Set current_property to current_property concatenated with char
    Otherwise if in_rule and in_property:
    Set current_value to current_value concatenated with char Set i to i 1 Return css_properties

Process called "replace_pattern" that takes text as String and pattern as String and replacement as String returns String:
    Note: Replace all occurrences of pattern in text with replacement
    If length of pattern is equal to 0:
    Return text Note: Empty pattern returns original text Let result be ""
    Let i be 0
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let pattern_length be length of pattern While i is less than text_length:
    Note: Check if pattern matches at current position
    Let pattern_matches be true
    If i pattern_length is less than or equal to text_length:
    For j from 0 to (pattern_length - 1):
    If get_character_at_index with string as text and index as (i j) is not equal to get_character_at_index with string as pattern and index as j:
    Set pattern_matches to false
    Break from loop
    Otherwise:
    Set pattern_matches to false If pattern_matches:
    Set result to result concatenated with replacement
    Set i to i pattern_length
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result concatenated with get_character_at_index with string as text and index as i
    Set i to i 1 Return result

Process called "serialize_config_to_dict" that takes config as FormatterConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Serialize formatter config to dictionary
    Return dictionary containing
    "output_format" as format_output_format with format as config.output_format,
    "color_scheme" as format_color_scheme with scheme as config.color_scheme,
    "verbosity_level" as format_verbosity_level with level as config.verbosity_level,
    "max_frames" as config.max_frames,
    "show_source_context" as config.show_source_context,
    "show_variables" as config.show_variables,
    "show_performance_metrics" as config.show_performance_metrics

Process called "serialize_frame_to_dict" that takes frame as TracebackCore.StackFrame and config as FormatterConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Serialize stack frame to dictionary
    Return dictionary containing
    "function_name" as frame.function_name,
    "file_path" as frame.file_path,
    "line_number" as frame.line_number,
    "column_number" as frame.column_number,
    "source_line" as frame.source_line,
    "execution_time_nanoseconds" as frame.execution_time_nanoseconds,
    "memory_usage_bytes" as frame.memory_usage_bytes

Process called "serialize_dictionary_to_json" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Serialize dictionary to JSON string with proper key-value serialization
    Let json_result be "{"
    Let keys be get_dictionary_keys with dict as data
    Let key_count be length of keys
    Let current_index be 0 For each key in keys:
    Let value be data[key]
    Let serialized_key be "\"" concatenated with escape_json_string with text as key concatenated with "\""
    Let serialized_value be format_json_value with value as value Set json_result to json_result concatenated with serialized_key concatenated with ":" concatenated with serialized_value If current_index is less than (key_count - 1):
    Set json_result to json_result concatenated with ","
    Set current_index to current_index 1 Set json_result to json_result concatenated with "}"
    Return json_result

Process called "format_output_format" that takes format as OutputFormat returns String:
    Note: Format output format for display
    If format is equal to PlainText:
    Return "plain_text"
    Otherwise if format is equal to ColoredTerminal:
    Return "colored_terminal"
    Otherwise if format is equal to HTML:
    Return "html"
    Otherwise if format is equal to JSON:
    Return "json"
    Otherwise if format is equal to XML:
    Return "xml"
    Otherwise if format is equal to Markdown:
    Return "markdown"
    Otherwise:
    Return "unknown"

Note: Advanced feature implementation functions
Process called "generate_html_styles" that takes config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate comprehensive HTML styles based on configuration
    Let color_palette be get_color_palette_for_scheme with scheme as config.color_scheme
    Let font_config be get_font_configuration with theme as config.theme_name Let base_styles be "<style>\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with "body {\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " font-family: " concatenated with font_config["family"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " font-size: " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as font_config["size"] concatenated with "px;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " line-height: " concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as font_config["line_height"] and precision as 2 concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " background-color: " concatenated with color_palette["background"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " color: " concatenated with color_palette["foreground"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " margin: 20px;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " padding: 0;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with ".traceback-container {\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " border: 1px solid " concatenated with color_palette["accent"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " border-radius: 8px;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " padding: 20px;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " background-color: " concatenated with color_palette["background"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with ".traceback-title {\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " color: " concatenated with color_palette["accent"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " font-weight: bold;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " margin-bottom: 10px;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with ".frame {\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " border-left: 3px solid " concatenated with color_palette["accent"] concatenated with ";\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " padding-left: 15px;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " margin: 10px 0;\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with " background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with "}\n\n"
    If length of config.custom_css is greater than 0:
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with config.custom_css concatenated with "\n"
    Set base_styles to base_styles concatenated with "</style>"
    Return base_styles

Process called "generate_html_frame" that takes frame as TracebackCore.StackFrame and index as Integer and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate comprehensive HTML frame with full details and styling
    Let frame_html be "<div class=\"frame\" id=\"frame-" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as index concatenated with "\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <div class=\"frame-header\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"frame-number\">Frame " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as index concatenated with ":</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"function-name\" onclick=\"showFunctionDetails('" concatenated with frame.function_name concatenated with "')\">" concatenated with frame.function_name concatenated with "</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </div>\n\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <div class=\"frame-location\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"location-label\">Location:</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <a href=\"file://" concatenated with frame.file_path concatenated with "#L" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as frame.line_number concatenated with "\" class=\"file-link\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " " concatenated with frame.file_path concatenated with ":" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as frame.line_number
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </a>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </div>\n\n"
    If config.show_source_context:
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <div class=\"source-context\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"source-label\">Source:</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <pre class=\"source-code\">" concatenated with escape_html_content with text as frame.source_line concatenated with "</pre>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </div>\n\n"
    If config.show_performance_metrics and frame.execution_time_nanoseconds is greater than 0:
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <div class=\"performance-metrics\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"perf-label\">Performance:</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"exec-time\">" concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as frame.execution_time_nanoseconds concatenated with "</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"memory-usage\">" concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as frame.memory_usage_bytes concatenated with "</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </div>\n\n"
    If config.show_variables and length of frame.local_variables is greater than 0:
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <div class=\"variables-section\">\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <span class=\"variables-label\">Local Variables:</span>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <ul class=\"variables-list\">\n"
    For each var_name and var_value in frame.local_variables:
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " <li><span class=\"var-name\">" concatenated with var_name concatenated with ":</span> <span class=\"var-value\">" concatenated with format_variable_value with value as var_value concatenated with "</span></li>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </ul>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with " </div>\n"
    Set frame_html to frame_html concatenated with "</div>\n"
    Return frame_html

Process called "generate_html_javascript" returns String:
    Note: Generate comprehensive JavaScript for interactive features
    Let js_code be "<script>\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "function showFunctionDetails(functionName) {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " const detailsPanel = document.getElementById('function-details-panel') || createDetailsPanel();\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " detailsPanel.innerHTML = '<h3>Function: ' concatenated with functionName concatenated with '</h3>';\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " detailsPanel.innerHTML concatenated with '= '<p>Click on frames to see more details.</p>';\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " detailsPanel.style.display = 'block';\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "function createDetailsPanel() {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " const panel = document.createElement('div');\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " panel.id = 'function-details-panel';\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " panel.style.cssText = 'position:fixed;top:20px;right:20px;width:300px;background:#f0f0f0;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:15px;border-radius:8px;z-index:1000;display:none;';\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " document.body.appendChild(panel);\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " return panel;\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "function openSourceFile(filePath, lineNumber) {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " window.open('file://' concatenated with filePath concatenated with '#L' concatenated with lineNumber, '_blank');\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "function toggleFrameExpansion(frameId) {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " const frame = document.getElementById(frameId);\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " const details = frame.querySelector('.frame-details');\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " if (details) {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " details.style.display = details.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " }\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "}\n\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " console.log('RUNA Traceback Interactive Features Loaded');\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " const frames = document.querySelectorAll('.frame');\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " frames.forEach((frame, index) => {\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " frame.addEventListener('click', () => toggleFrameExpansion('frame-' concatenated with index));\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with " });\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "});\n\n"
    Set js_code to js_code concatenated with "</script>"
    Return js_code

Process called "generate_exception_content_with_analysis" that takes exception_info as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and analysis as TracebackAnalyzer.StackAnalysisResult and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate comprehensive exception content with detailed analysis
    Let content be "=== RUNA EXCEPTION ANALYSIS ===\n\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Exception Type: " concatenated with exception_info.exception_type concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Message: " concatenated with exception_info.exception_message concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Timestamp: " concatenated with format_current_timestamp concatenated with "\n\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== ANALYSIS RESULTS ===\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Root Cause Confidence: " concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as analysis.confidence_score and precision as 2 concatenated with "%\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Performance Impact: " concatenated with format_performance_impact with impact as analysis.performance_impact concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Memory Impact: " concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as analysis.memory_impact_bytes concatenated with "\n\n"
    If length of analysis.root_causes is greater than 0:
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== ROOT CAUSES ===\n"
    For each cause in analysis.root_causes:
    Set content to content concatenated with "- " concatenated with cause concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "\n"
    If length of exception_info.suggestions is greater than 0:
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== SUGGESTED FIXES ===\n"
    For each suggestion in exception_info.suggestions:
    Set content to content concatenated with "- " concatenated with suggestion concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== STACK ANALYSIS ===\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Total Frames: " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as length of exception_info.stack_frames concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Problematic Frames: " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as analysis.problematic_frame_count concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Critical Path Length: " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as analysis.critical_path_length concatenated with "\n\n"
    Return content

Process called "generate_exception_interactive_elements" that takes exception_info as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and analysis as TracebackAnalyzer.StackAnalysisResult and config as FormatterConfig returns List[InteractiveElement]:
    Return list containing

Process called "generate_performance_visual_content" that takes profile as TracebackAnalyzer.PerformanceProfile and config as FormatterConfig returns String:
    Note: Generate comprehensive performance visual content with detailed metrics
    Let content be "=== RUNA PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS ===\n\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Overall Performance Score: " concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as profile.performance_score and precision as 2 concatenated with "/100\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Analysis Timestamp: " concatenated with format_current_timestamp concatenated with "\n\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== EXECUTION METRICS ===\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Total Execution Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as profile.total_execution_time_ns concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Average Frame Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as (profile.total_execution_time_ns divided by profile.total_frames) concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Peak Memory Usage: " concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as profile.peak_memory_bytes concatenated with "\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "Memory Efficiency: " concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as profile.memory_efficiency and precision as 2 concatenated with "%\n\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== PERFORMANCE BREAKDOWN ===\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "CPU Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as profile.cpu_time_ns concatenated with " (" concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as ((profile.cpu_time_ns divided by profile.total_execution_time_ns) multiplied by 100) and precision as 1 concatenated with "%)\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "I/O Wait Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as profile.io_wait_time_ns concatenated with " (" concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as ((profile.io_wait_time_ns divided by profile.total_execution_time_ns) multiplied by 100) and precision as 1 concatenated with "%)\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "GC Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as profile.gc_time_ns concatenated with " (" concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as ((profile.gc_time_ns divided by profile.total_execution_time_ns) multiplied by 100) and precision as 1 concatenated with "%)\n\n"
    Set content to content concatenated with "=== OPTIMIZATION OPPORTUNITIES ===\n"
    If profile.cpu_time_ns is greater than (profile.total_execution_time_ns multiplied by 70 divided by 100):
    Set content to content concatenated with "- High CPU usage detected. Consider algorithmic optimizations.\n"
    If profile.io_wait_time_ns is greater than (profile.total_execution_time_ns multiplied by 30 divided by 100):
    Set content to content concatenated with "- Significant I/O wait time. Consider async operations or caching.\n"
    If profile.gc_time_ns is greater than (profile.total_execution_time_ns multiplied by 15 divided by 100):
    Set content to content concatenated with "- High garbage collection overhead. Review memory allocation patterns.\n"
    If profile.peak_memory_bytes is greater than 104857600: Note: >100MB
    Set content to content concatenated with "- High memory usage detected. Consider memory optimization techniques.\n"
    Return content

Process called "generate_performance_charts" that takes profile as TracebackAnalyzer.PerformanceProfile and config as FormatterConfig returns List[String]:
    Note: Generate performance charts based on profile data
    Let charts be list containing Note: CPU usage breakdown chart
    If profile.cpu_time_ns is greater than 0:
    Let cpu_chart be "CPU_Usage_Breakdown_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as (profile.cpu_time_ns divided by 1000000)
    Add to charts cpu_chart Note: Memory usage timeline chart
    If profile.peak_memory_bytes is greater than 0:
    Let memory_chart be "Memory_Timeline_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as (profile.peak_memory_bytes divided by 1024)
    Add to charts memory_chart Note: I/O wait time analysis chart
    If profile.io_wait_time_ns is greater than 0:
    Let io_chart be "IO_Wait_Analysis_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as (profile.io_wait_time_ns divided by 1000000)
    Add to charts io_chart Note: Garbage collection impact chart
    If profile.gc_time_ns is greater than 0:
    Let gc_chart be "GC_Impact_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as (profile.gc_time_ns divided by 1000000)
    Add to charts gc_chart Note: Performance score trend chart
    Let score_chart be "Performance_Score_Trend_" concatenated with convert_float_to_string with number as profile.performance_score and precision as 1
    Add to charts score_chart Return charts

Process called "generate_performance_interactive_elements" that takes profile as TracebackAnalyzer.PerformanceProfile and charts as List[String] returns List[InteractiveElement]:
    Note: Generate interactive elements for performance visualization
    Let elements be list containing Note: Chart interaction elements
    For i from 0 to (length of charts - 1):
    Let chart_element be InteractiveElement with:
    element_type as ExpandableFrame
    element_id as "chart_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as i
    coordinates as ElementCoordinates with:
    start_line as i times 3 1,
    start_column as 5,
    end_line as i times 3 2,
    end_column as 50
    action_handler as "toggleChartExpansion('chart_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as i concatenated with "')"
    tooltip_text as "Click to expand/collapse " concatenated with charts[i]
    metadata as dictionary containing "chart_type" as charts[i], "profile_score" as profile.performance_score
    Add to elements chart_element Note: Performance metric hover elements
    Let cpu_element be InteractiveElement with:
    element_type as HoverableVariable
    element_id as "cpu_metrics"
    coordinates as ElementCoordinates with:
    start_line as 10,
    start_column as 15,
    end_line as 10,
    end_column as 35
    action_handler as "showCPUDetails()"
    tooltip_text as "CPU Time: " concatenated with format_nanoseconds_human with nanos as profile.cpu_time_ns
    metadata as dictionary containing "metric_type" as "cpu", "value" as profile.cpu_time_ns
    Add to elements cpu_element Let memory_element be InteractiveElement with:
    element_type as HoverableVariable
    element_id as "memory_metrics"
    coordinates as ElementCoordinates with:
    start_line as 11,
    start_column as 15,
    end_line as 11,
    end_column as 40
    action_handler as "showMemoryDetails()"
    tooltip_text as "Peak Memory: " concatenated with format_bytes_human with bytes as profile.peak_memory_bytes
    metadata as dictionary containing "metric_type" as "memory", "value" as profile.peak_memory_bytes
    Add to elements memory_element Return elements

