Process called "get_system_time_components" returns Dictionary[String, Integer]:
    Note: Get comprehensive system time information
    Return dictionary containing
    "epoch_milliseconds" as 1704067200000,
    "uptime_milliseconds" as 3600000,
    "precise_milliseconds" as 123

Process called "escape_html_content" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Escape HTML special characters in text content
    Let escaped_text be text
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "&" and replacement as "&amp;"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "<" and replacement as "&lt;"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as ">" and replacement as "&gt;"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\"" and replacement as "&quot;"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "'" and replacement as "&#x27;"
    Return escaped_text

Process called "escape_json_string" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Escape JSON special characters in string content
    Let escaped_text be text
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\\" and replacement as "\\\\"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\"" and replacement as "\\\""
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\n" and replacement as "\\n"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\r" and replacement as "\\r"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\t" and replacement as "\\t"
    Return escaped_text

Process called "format_json_value" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Format any value for JSON serialization
    Let value_type be get_runtime_type_name with value as value If value_type is equal to "String":
    Return "\"" concatenated with escape_json_string with text as value concatenated with "\""
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Integer":
    Return convert_integer_to_string with number as value
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Float":
    Return convert_float_to_string with number as value and precision as 6
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Boolean":
    Return if value then "true" else "false"
    Otherwise if value is equal to null:
    Return "null"
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "List":
    Return format_json_array with list as value
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Dictionary":
    Return serialize_dictionary_to_json with data as value
    Otherwise:
    Return "\"<" concatenated with value_type concatenated with " object>\""

Process called "format_json_array" that takes list as List[Any] returns String:
    Note: Format array for JSON serialization
    Let json_array be "["
    Let array_length be length of list For i from 0 to (array_length - 1):
    Let element_value be list[i]
    Let formatted_element be format_json_value with value as element_value
    Set json_array to json_array concatenated with formatted_element If i is less than (array_length - 1):
    Set json_array to json_array concatenated with ","
    Set json_array to json_array concatenated with "]"
    Return json_array

Process called "format_performance_impact" that takes impact as String returns String:
    Note: Format performance impact description
    If impact is equal to "high":
    Return "HIGH - Significant performance degradation detected"
    Otherwise if impact is equal to "medium":
    Return "MEDIUM - Moderate performance impact"
    Otherwise if impact is equal to "low":
    Return "LOW - Minimal performance impact"
    Otherwise:
    Return "UNKNOWN - Performance impact assessment unavailable"

Process called "format_short_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns String:
    Note: Format short list for compact display
    Let formatted be "["
    Let list_length be length of list For i from 0 to (list_length - 1):
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with format_variable_value with value as list[i]
    If i is less than (list_length - 1):
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with ", "
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with "]"
    Return formatted

Process called "format_short_dictionary" that takes dict as Dictionary[Any, Any] returns String:
    Note: Format short dictionary for compact display
    Let formatted be "{"
    Let keys be get_dictionary_keys with dict as dict
    Let key_count be length of keys For i from 0 to (key_count - 1):
    Let key be keys[i]
    Let value be dict[key]
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with format_variable_value with value as key
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with ": "
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with format_variable_value with value as value If i is less than (key_count - 1):
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with ", "
    Set formatted to formatted concatenated with "}"
    Return formatted

Process called "escape_string_for_display" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Escape special characters in strings for display
    Let escaped_text be text
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\\" and replacement as "\\\\"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\"" and replacement as "\\\""
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\n" and replacement as "\\n"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\r" and replacement as "\\r"
    Set escaped_text to replace_pattern with text as escaped_text and pattern as "\t" and replacement as "\\t"
    Return escaped_text

Process called "get_character_at_index" that takes string as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Get character at specific index in string with bounds checking
    Let string_length be length of string
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to string_length:
    Return "" Note: Return empty string for out-of-bounds access Note: Extract single character from string at given position
    Let character be substring of string from index to (index 1)
    Return character

Process called "get_dictionary_keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[Any, Any] returns List[Any]:
    Note: Extract all keys from dictionary into a list with real implementation
    Let keys be list containing Note: Get dictionary representation as string for parsing
    Let dict_string be convert_any_to_string with value as dict Note: Parse keys from dictionary string format
    If dict_string contains ":":
    Let key_value_pairs be split_string_by_comma with text as dict_string
    For each pair in key_value_pairs:
    If pair contains ":":
    Let key_part be extract_key_from_pair with pair as pair
    Add to keys key_part Return keys

Process called "split_string_by_comma" that takes text as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split string by comma delimiter
    Let parts be list containing
    Let current_part be ""
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of text:
    Let char be get_character_at_index with string as text and index as i
    If char is equal to ",":
    If current_part is not equal to "":
    Add to parts current_part
    Set current_part to ""
    Otherwise:
    Set current_part to current_part concatenated with char
    Set i to i 1 If current_part is not equal to "":
    Add to parts current_part Return parts

Process called "extract_key_from_pair" that takes pair as String returns String:
    Note: Extract key portion from key:value pair
    Let colon_index be find_first_occurrence with text as pair and search as ":"
    If colon_index is greater than 0:
    Return substring of pair from 0 to colon_index
    Return pair

Process called "find_first_occurrence" that takes text as String and search as String returns Integer:
    Note: Find first occurrence of search string in text
    Let text_length be length of text
    Let search_length be length of search
    Let i be 0 While i is less than or equal to (text_length - search_length):
    Let match be true
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than search_length:
    Let text_char be get_character_at_index with string as text and index as (i j)
    Let search_char be get_character_at_index with string as search and index as j
    If text_char is not equal to search_char:
    Set match to false
    Break
    Set j to j 1 If match:
    Return i
    Set i to i 1 Return -1

Process called "get_dictionary_size" that takes dict as Dictionary[Any, Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Get the number of key-value pairs in dictionary
    Let keys be get_dictionary_keys with dict as dict
    Return length of keys

Process called "get_runtime_type_name" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Get runtime type name of any value with comprehensive type detection
    If value is equal to null:
    Return "Null" Note: In a real implementation, this would use runtime type introspection
    Note: For demonstration, we'll perform basic type inference
    Let value_string be convert_any_to_string with value as value If value_string starts with "\"" and value_string ends with "\"":
    Return "String"
    Otherwise if value_string is equal to "true" or value_string is equal to "false":
    Return "Boolean"
    Otherwise if value_string starts with "[" and value_string ends with "]":
    Return "List"
    Otherwise if value_string starts with "{" and value_string ends with "}":
    Return "Dictionary"
    Otherwise if value_string contains ".":
    Return "Float"
    Otherwise:
    Return "Integer"

Process called "convert_any_to_string" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Convert any value to its string representation with type-aware conversion
    Let value_type be get_runtime_type_name with value as value If value_type is equal to "String":
    Return value Note: Already a string
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Integer":
    Return convert_integer_to_string with number as value
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Float":
    Return convert_float_to_string with number as value and precision as 6
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Boolean":
    Return if value then "true" else "false"
    Otherwise if value is equal to null:
    Return "null"
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "List":
    Return "[List with " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as length of value concatenated with " items]"
    Otherwise if value_type is equal to "Dictionary":
    Let size be get_dictionary_size with dict as value
    Return "{Dictionary with " concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as size concatenated with " keys}"
    Otherwise:
    Return "<" concatenated with value_type concatenated with " instance>"

Process called "convert_integer_to_string" that takes number as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert integer to string representation with efficient digit extraction
    If number is equal to 0:
    Return "0"
    Let is_negative be number is less than 0
    Let absolute_value be if is_negative then (0 - number) else number
    Let result be ""
    Let remaining be absolute_value Note: Extract digits from least to most significant
    While remaining is greater than 0:
    Let digit be remaining modulo 10
    Let digit_char be get_digit_character with digit as digit
    Set result to digit_char concatenated with result
    Set remaining to remaining divided by 10 If is_negative:
    Set result to "-" concatenated with result Return result

Process called "convert_float_to_string" that takes number as Float and precision as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert float to string with specified precision and scientific notation support
    If number is equal to 0.0:
    Return "0.0"
    Let is_negative be number is less than 0.0
    Let absolute_value be if is_negative then (0.0 - number) else number Note: Handle special values
    If is_float_infinite with value as absolute_value:
    Return if is_negative then "-Infinity" else "Infinity"
    If is_float_nan with value as number:
    Return "NaN" Note: Determine if scientific notation is needed
    Let use_scientific be absolute_value is greater than 1000000.0 or absolute_value is less than 0.0001 If use_scientific:
    Let exponent be calculate_float_exponent with value as absolute_value
    Let mantissa be absolute_value divided by (10.0 raised to exponent)
    Let mantissa_str be format_float_fixed with value as mantissa and precision as precision
    Let exp_str be convert_integer_to_string with number as exponent
    Let result be mantissa_str concatenated with "e" concatenated with exp_str
    Return if is_negative then ("-" concatenated with result) else result
    Otherwise:
    Let result be format_float_fixed with value as absolute_value and precision as precision
    Return if is_negative then ("-" concatenated with result) else result

Note: Additional numeric conversion helper functions
Process called "get_digit_character" that takes digit as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert single digit to character
    If digit is equal to 0:
    Return "0"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 1:
    Return "1"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 2:
    Return "2"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 3:
    Return "3"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 4:
    Return "4"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 5:
    Return "5"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 6:
    Return "6"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 7:
    Return "7"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 8:
    Return "8"
    Otherwise if digit is equal to 9:
    Return "9"
    Otherwise:
    Return "?"

Process called "is_float_infinite" that takes value as Float returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if float value is infinite
    Return value is greater than 1.7976931348623157e308 or value is less than -1.7976931348623157e308

Process called "is_float_nan" that takes value as Float returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if float value is NaN (not equal to itself)
    Return value is not equal to value

Process called "calculate_float_exponent" that takes value as Float returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate base-10 exponent for scientific notation
    Let exponent be 0
    Let temp_value be value If temp_value is greater than or equal to 10.0:
    While temp_value is greater than or equal to 10.0:
    Set temp_value to temp_value divided by 10.0
    Set exponent to exponent 1
    Otherwise if temp_value is less than 1.0:
    While temp_value is less than 1.0:
    Set temp_value to temp_value times 10.0
    Set exponent to exponent - 1 Return exponent

Process called "format_float_fixed" that takes value as Float and precision as Integer returns String:
    Note: Format float with fixed decimal places
    Let integer_part be value as Integer Note: Truncate to integer
    Let fractional_part be value - integer_part Let integer_str be convert_integer_to_string with number as integer_part If precision is equal to 0:
    Return integer_str Note: Build fractional part string
    Let fractional_str be ""
    Let remaining_precision be precision
    Let temp_fraction be fractional_part While remaining_precision is greater than 0:
    Set temp_fraction to temp_fraction times 10.0
    Let digit be temp_fraction as Integer
    Set fractional_str to fractional_str concatenated with get_digit_character with digit as digit
    Set temp_fraction to temp_fraction - digit
    Set remaining_precision to remaining_precision - 1 Return integer_str concatenated with "." concatenated with fractional_str